{"id":"3975","name":"happy-hour-we-have-a-twittergate","title":"Happy Hour: We Have A Twittergate!","author":"Christy Frink","date":"2010-02-17T18:00:00-06:00","tags":["erik cole","health &amp; wellness","jamie hollin","john cooper","open meetings act","remote starters","twitter","twittergate","williamson county"],"categories":["News"],"contentEncoded":"<div id=\"greet_block\"><noscript><div class=\"greet_block wpgb_cornered\"><div class=\"greet_text\"><div class=\"greet_image\"><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/feed/rss/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://nashvillest.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-greet-box/images/rss_icon.png\" alt=\"WP Greet Box icon\"></a></div>Hello there! If you&apos;re new to Nashvillest, you might want to <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/nashvillest\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>subscribe to our RSS feed</strong></a> to make sure you don&apos;t miss anything! We&apos;re also on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/#!/nashvillest\" target=\"blank\"><strong>Twitter</strong></a> if you&apos;d like to join us there!<div style=\"clear:both\"></div><div class=\"greet_block_powered_by\">Powered by <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/projects/wordpress-plugins/wp-greet-box-wordpress-plugin/\" title=\"WP Greet Box WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WP Greet Box</a> <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/\" title=\"WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WordPress Plugin</a></div><div style=\"clear:both\"></div></div></div></noscript></div><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/bdesham/4327077290/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.flickr.com&apos;]);\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2787/4327077290_f9433b1b03.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"333\"></a></p><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><ul><li>Councilman Jamie Hollin, the District 5 Metro councilman, has taken to the blogosphere when it comes to the whole to-twitter-or-not-to-twitter debate. After a Council attorney advised that tweeting during Metro Council meetings could be a violation of the Open Meetings Act, Councilman Hollin is putting the question to his constituents. [<a href=\"http://jamiehollin.wordpress.com/2010/02/17/twitter-vel-non/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;jamiehollin.wordpress.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Jamie Hollin</a> via <a href=\"http://politics.nashvillepost.com/2010/02/17/council-attorney-says-twitter-ban-talk-just-a-misunderstanding/?utm_source=feedburner&amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;utm_campaign=Feed%3A+postpolitics+%28Post+Politics%29&amp;utm_content=Google+Reader\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;politics.nashvillepost.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Post Politics</a>]</li><li>Councilman Erik Cole, meanwhile, continues to tweet circles around the rest of the council. Non-deliberatively, of course. [<a href=\"http://twitter.com/district7/status/9256965168\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;twitter.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">@district7</a>]</li><li>And now the councilmen are chattering back and forth on Twitter about outfoxing the Twitter police. These are the moments we live for in local politics. [<a href=\"http://twitter.com/jrhollin/status/9257121988\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;twitter.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">@jrhollin</a>]</li><li>Oh, but Council attorney John Cooper (whose words incited the Twitter panic in the first place) claims he never said that council members couldn&#x2019;t tweet; they just can&#x2019;t <em>deliberate</em>. This is what everyone has been saying all day long. [<a href=\"http://politics.nashvillepost.com/2010/02/17/council-attorney-says-twitter-ban-talk-just-a-misunderstanding/?utm_source=feedburner&amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;utm_campaign=Feed%3A+postpolitics+%28Post+Politics%29&amp;utm_content=Google+Reader\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;politics.nashvillepost.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Post Politics</a>]</li><li>And moving onto some non-Twitter news, you can now warm up your car in peace. But only if you have a remote starter. [<a href=\"http://www.wkrn.com/global/story.asp?s=11995789\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wkrn.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">WKRN</a>]</li><li>Congrats to Williamson County as they are now the healthiest county in the state. [<a href=\"http://www.wsmv.com/health/22590362/detail.html\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wsmv.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">WSMV</a>]</li><li>And a bigger congrats to our city because we finally achieved temperatures above freezing today. [<a href=\"http://nashvillewx.com/2010/02/noon-nashville-finally-above-freezing/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;nashvillewx.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Nashville WX</a>]</li></ul></p><p><em>Photo by </em><a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/bdesham/4327077290/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.flickr.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\"><em>bdesham</em></a><em>.</em></p><p>Related posts:<ol><li><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/2010/02/17/bright-early-twittering-no-more-edition/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: Bright &amp; Early: Twittering No More Edition\">Bright &amp; Early: Twittering No More Edition</a></li></ol></p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<!--END .entry-content .article-->"}